characteristics:
Small Evergreen trees; branchlets hirsute when young.
Leaves thinly coriaceous, rhombic-oblong, 3-5 cm long, 1.4-2.1 cm broad, acute or rarely obtuse at apex, cuneate at base, margins slightly revolute, glabrous above, glaucous beneath, lateral veins ca. 4-6 pairs, indistinct above, slightly elevated beneath, veinlets indistinct, parallel veinlets not present at base of blade; petioles 3-5 mm long, tomentose.
Pistillate flowers subsessile; receptacle short, 1 mm long, villous outside; tepals 6, oblong, 1.5 mm long, 0.7 mm broad, obtuse at apex; staminodes filiform, 1.2 mm long, hirsute; 3rd whorl glandular; ovary ovoid 0.6 mm long, glabrous, style 2 mm long, sparsely villous;
Fruit ellipsoid, 0.7 cm long;

Small Evergreen trees; trunk 4 m tall; branchlets pubescent; buds elliptic-oblong, acute at apex, obtuse at base, scales brownish-pubescent.
Leaves alternate, lanceolate to oblong, 7-9 cm long, 2.5-3.5 cm broad, slightly lustrous above, glaucous and yellow-gray appressed pubescent beneath, glabrous when young, thinly coriaceous, acute rarely acuminate at apex, acute to acuminate at base, with 3 main veins, midrib flattened above, elevated beneath, lateral veins 4-5 pairs, veinlets subparallel, flattened to somewhat elevated beneath; petioles 0.5-1.2 cm long, brownish-puberulent.
Inflorescences globose in buds, sessile, solitary to 4-5 clustered, axillary or lateral; involucral bracts 4-5, elliptic, puberulent outside, caducous; flowers red; staminate flowers with receptacle broadly campanulate, tomentose out-side; tepals 4, broadly elliptic, 3 mm long, slightly tomentose outside, glabrous inside; fertile stamens 6, filaments 4 mm long, hirsute at base, 3rd whorl of stamens with glands, anthers oblong, 1.5 mm long, 4-celled; reduced ovary densely hirsute; pistillate flowers with styles long and fine-hairy;
Berry ellipsoid, 1 cm long; pedicels 7 mm long, blackish-violet;
